dynamics of the human psyche, how trauma affects the psyche and how to facilitate resolution to long standing issues. More than just a technique, DMP® addresses core soul wounds and facilitates soul retrieval beyond the current life and integration of these lost parts. Deep Memory Process® has transformed the lives of thousands of individuals and changed the way many others perform therapy and healing with their clients. DMP transforms body, mind, emotion and spirit simultaneously and the results for clients can be profound.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Admission requirements</strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Trainings are open to individuals with an interest in regression therapy and practitioners in the healing professions, the following list is not exclusive but includes :</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Health professionals, GPs, care workers, Psychotherapists, Psychologists / Psychiatrists, Hypnotherapists, Regression TherapistsPsychosynthesis, transpersonal psychology, hypnotherapy, Gestalt therapy, Psychodrama, Rebirthing, Breath work, past life therapy, nurses and complementary health professionals. Energy healers, Holistic therapists, shamanism, Reiki, medicine, and nursing, as well as for spiritual counsellors &amp; trainers, massage practitioners, body workers.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Training</strong> in Deep Memory Process® is divided into four modules, each lasting 5 days. The first two modules offer a certificate in Basic Past Life Therapy, with full certification in Deep Memory Process offered after completion of all four modules and case study requirements.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">The four training modules are designed to be taken in two stages: two basic modules: levels 1 &amp; 2, followed by two advanced modules: levels 3 &amp; 4.Each training module contains lecture, discussion, demonstration and group processing. The trainings are designed to be highly self-experiential and personally transformative, held preferably in a retreat format , so that participants are able to deeply immerse themselves in the process. Depending on the various factors, usually with supervision we aim for you to guide and receive swop sessions in each training.</p>";s:14:"element_scheme";s:0:"";s:9:"stb_title";s:0:"";s:17:"stb_title_heading";s:2:"h3";s:9:"stb_style";s:6:"style1";s:11:"top_padding";s:2:"20";s:14:"bottom_padding";s:2:"10";s:18:"znpb_hide_visitors";s:3:"all";s:9:"css_class";s:0:"";}s:7:"content";a:0:{}s:5:"width";s:0:"";s:6:"widget";s:0:"";s:3:"uid";s:13:"eluid89e53c79";}}s:5:"width";s:9:"col-md-12";s:6:"widget";s:0:"";s:3:"uid";s:13:"eluid6f3e0753";}i:1;a:6:{s:6:"object";s:8:"ZnColumn";s:7:"options";a:0:{}s:7:"content";a:0:{}s:5:"width";s:9:"col-md-12";s:6:"widget";s:0:"";s:3:"uid";s:13:"eluid34b3d89b";}}s:5:"width";s:0:"";s:6:"widget";s:0:"";s:3:"uid";s:13:"eluid297ad8d1";}i:3;a:6:{s:6:"object";s:9:"ZnSection";s:7:"options";a:0:{}s:7:"content";a:4:{i:0;a:6:{s:6:"object";s:8:"ZnColumn";s:7:"options";a:0:{}s:7:"content";a:1:{i:0;a:6:{s:6:"object";s:13:"TH_ServiceBox";s:7:"options";a:12:{s:9:"sbx_style";s:5:"boxed";s:14:"element_scheme";s:0:"";s:17:"service_box_title";s:21:"Module 1: Basic Level";s:16:"service_box_desc";s:45:"Running the Story with Core Emotional Release";s:20:"service_box_features";s:744:"Regression as active embodiment (psychodrama); Understanding the process of assessing clients to explore background history and other possible influences on their presenting issues. Choosing which charged key phrases to use from the interview. Understanding the various methods of inductions; how to guide a past life story; working in the “now” of the story, observing body cues and energy movements, using and working with resistance and blocks; dramatic tension; learn the importance of and how to facilitate healing catharsis; symbolic resonance; introduction to working in the after-life states (Bardos) 