(2004, 1, '2016-07-17 14:58:59', '2016-07-17 14:58:59', '<div class="Normal-P-P5"><span class="Emphasis-C">The Holy Grail: Healing the Sexual Wound in the Western Psyche by renowned Jungian psychologist Roger J. Woolger. This would not be Mr.</span><span class="Normal-C-C15">Woolger’s first foray into audio. He has published several with the Sounds True label who also records and distributes Eckhart Tolle among others. With degrees from Oxford and London Universities as well as the C.G. Jung Institute in Zurich, Roger developed a practice of spiritual psychotherapy he terms Deep Memory Process which he use to teach in Europe and the U.S. Roger’s eloquent and clear narration is the perfect vehicle for Jungian thought as well as any classical or philosophical text. Comprehensive ideas are rendered </span><span class="Normal-C-C16">accessible and his heartfelt delivery was as enjoyable to listen to as any welcomed guest.\n</span></div>\n<div class="Normal-P-P4"><span class="Normal-C-C16"> </span></div>\n<div class="Normal-P-P6"><span class="Normal-C-C17">Topics include:  </span><span class="Normal-C-C16">The Troubadors, The Cult of the Lady, The Psychological Significance of Chivalry and Perceval the Hero</span></div>', 'The Holy Grail: Healing the Sexual Wound in the Western Psyche', 'Pellentesque habitant morbi tristique senectus et netus et malesuada fames ac turpis egestas. Vestibulum tortor quam, feugiat vitae, ultricies eget, tempor sit amet, ante. Donec eu libero sit amet quam egestas semper. Aenean ultricies mi vitae est. Mauris placerat eleifend leo.', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '1511-autosave-v1', '', '', '2016-07-17 14:58:59', '2016-07-17 14:58:59', '', 1511, 'http://gmswebdesign.net/spiritual1/2016/07/17/1511-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
