(2312, 1, '2016-09-26 11:46:52', '2016-09-26 11:46:52', '<p class="Wp-Normal2-P"><span class="Normal2-C-C3">Module 2 -<wbr /> Working with Spirit and Transition</span></p>\r\n<p class="Wp-Normal2-P"><span class="Normal2-C-C4">Topics:The interlife or ‘Bardo’ phase; unfinished business with persons on earth; life review; reconciliation and forgiveness; integration of soul-<wbr />fragments, mediation and use of spirit helpers and guides; animal spirits; ancestors; levels of Bardo reality.</span></p>\r\n<p class="Wp-Normal2-P"><span class="Normal2-C-C2">Module 3  -<wbr /> Healing the Energy or Subtle Body</span></p>\r\n<p class="Wp-Normal2-P"><span class="Normal2-C-C5">Topics : Body or postural image; wounds to the</span></p>\r\n<p class="Wp-Normal2-P"><span class="Normal2-C-C5">etheric body; chronic holding patterns at death;</span></p>\r\n<p class="Wp-Normal2-P"><span class="Normal2-C-C5">letting the body tell its story; places of stored emotion in the body; strategies for release of body patterns in past lives and the ‘Bardos’.</span></p>\r\n<p class="Wp-Normal2-P"><span class="Normal2-C-C2">Module 4 -<wbr /></span></p>\r\n<p class="Wp-Normal2-P"><span class="Normal2-C-C2">Working with Residues of Trauma and Abuse: Dissociation and the Body</span></p>\r\n<p class="Wp-Normal2-P"><span class="Normal2-C-C2">T</span><span class="Normal2-C-C5">opics: Memory and the body; recognizing clinical “shock”; PTSD and dissociative states; trauma release and catharsis; reactions to sexual and physical abuse, chronic pain, torture and horror; collective unconscious bleed-<wbr />throughs from “past lives” and wounded “spirit” attachments; patterns of denial and chronic shut-<wbr />down; healing strategies; dialoguing with the body; working with breath and the body.</span></p>\r\n<p class="Wp-Normal2-P"><span class="Normal2-C-C5">To graduate as a DMP practitioner there are also practice sessions, personal work, supervision, written case work.(contact Juanita for these)</span></p>\r\n<p class="Wp-Normal2-P"><span class="Normal2-C">With Juanita Puddifoot to book -<wbr /> Tel : + 44 (0) 1234 350313   Email juanitac@btopenworld.com</span></p>', 'March friday 4th to 9th  2016', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '2039-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-09-26 11:46:52', '2016-09-26 11:46:52', '', 2039, 'http://egw.gmswebdesign.net/2039-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
